title: For Trade:  Wolf 7.62x39 unreliable
postcontent: This is, I'm guessing, about 600 to 700 rounds of Wolf FMJ 7.62x39. I only ever shot this ammunition from one rifle, an SKS, but about 3 out of every 10 rounds failed to fire. I'd guess it's the primers that are faulty as they were always fully struck but I'm not an expert. Most of the time the round would fire if I tried to shoot it again, but some of them wouldn't fire no matter what. I don't have a rifle in this caliber anymore so this stuff is just sitting around. I've been questioning myself whether it is ethical to sell/trade faulty ammunition but I decided to put it out there for two reasons.1. Having gone through about 300 rounds of this stuff I know that even though it's faulty it's not dangerous and I've fully disclosed my experience that it is unreliable.2. Even if nobody would want to shoot this ammunition there's probably a reloader out there who would be interested in a ton of bullets for next to nothing/for free.
